# PROJECT SETUP INSTRUCTIONS

1. Install Docker Desktop from [https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop) and make sure it is running.

2. (Windows Only) Enable WSL:

   * Open “Turn Windows features on or off”
   * Enable Windows Subsystem for Linux and Virtual Machine Platform
   * Restart your PC

3. Open Command Prompt as Administrator and run:
   wsl --install
   wsl --install -d Ubuntu

4. Clone the repository:
   git clone <your-repository-url>
   cd <project-folder-name>

5. Inside the project folder install dependencies:
   pip install airflow
   pip install -r requirements.txt

6. Start the services:
   docker compose up -d

7. Verify containers are running:
   docker ps

To stop services: docker compose down






